title: Video: Five best bakes in Great British Bake Off 2015
text: More than 12 million people are expected to tune into this year's finale of The Great British Bake Off , with the last episode expected to make it the most the most watched show of 2015. This year's show has once again seen some fantastic recipes scrutinised by judges Mary Berry and Paul Hollywood. Paul Jagger's lion loaf left Paul Hollywood very impressed (BBC) But which five bakes have come out on top? Mat's His 'n' Hers Vol-au-vents were popular (BBC) This video looks at some of the best bakes in the series. Radio Times of Great British Bake Off semi-finalists Nadiya Jamir Hussain (Jude Edginton/Immediate Media/Radio Times) Meanwhile, ahead of the finale David Cameron has revealed he will be rooting for Nadiya Jamir Hussain as she was "so cool under pressure" in reaching the last three of the popular TV contest. David Cameron will be watching the finale (Leon Neal/AFP/Getty Images) The Great British Bake Off finale airs on Wednesday October 7 at 8pm . TelegraphEnts Follow @telegraph
